'opt_sys_sprss'			=>	"Parameters for the standard RSS feed",
'opt_sys_sprssd'			=>	"You can specify the parameters that will be set to the RSS feed, which are necessary to support certain tags. This setting is intended only for experienced users, it is not recommended to change it if you do not know what these parameters are used.",
'opt_sys_tprss'			=>	"Parameters for Yandex Turbo RSS Feed",
'opt_sys_tprssd'			=>	"You can specify the parameters that will be set by Yandex Turbo RSS feed, which are necessary to support certain tags. This setting is intended only for experienced users, it is not recommended to change it if you do not know what these parameters are used.",
'opt_sys_dprss'			=>	"Parameters for Zen RSS Feed",
'opt_sys_dprssd'			=>	"You can specify the parameters that will be set to the Zen RSS feed, which are necessary to support certain tags. This setting is intended only for experienced users, it is not recommended to change it if you do not know what these parameters are used.",
'opt_sys_dsfield'			=>	"Hide the short description field when writing a publication",
'opt_sys_dsfieldd'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, the short description field will be hidden when writing a publication. This option is useful if the standard short description field is not used on the site and, for example, additional publication fields are used.",
'opt_sys_dffield'			=>	"Hide the full description field when writing a publication",
'opt_sys_dffieldd'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, the full description field will be hidden when writing a publication. This option is useful if the standard full description field is not used on the site and, for example, additional publication fields are used.",
'error_max_queue'			=>	"Yükləmə üçün icazə verilən maksimum fayl sayı aşılıb",
'files_public'			=>	"Public",
'files_private'			=>	"Private",
'opt_sys_fa'			=>	"File access mode for files",
'opt_sys_fad'			=>	"In this setting, you can specify which access rights will be assigned to the files after they are uploaded to the server. Private mode means that full access will be available only on behalf of the owner of the file on the server, public mode means that all users on the server are granted full access. For ease of file management, for example via FTP and on a local server, it is recommended to set public mode, however, some external services may require the mandatory inclusion of private mode. For example, Cloudflare S3 storage.",
'opt_sys_maxfilesh'			=>	"Package size in megabytes when uploading files",
'opt_sys_maxfileshd'			=>	"When uploading large files, these files are split into separate packages so as not to exceed the limits set on the server. You can specify the size of the data packet that will be sent to the server at a time, it is specified in megabytes. The fewer packets are sent, the faster the upload to the server will take place. This setting is intended for experienced users, do not change it if you do not know what it is intended for. The default packet size is 1.5, which means that packets of one and a half megabytes each will be sent.",
'opt_sys_imfs_7'			=>	"WebDAV Server",
'opt_sys_imfwe'			=>	"HTTP address WebDAV",
'opt_sys_imfwed'			=>	"Specify the HTTP URL to connect to the external WebDAV storage. For example https://website.com",
'opt_sys_imfweu'			=>	"Username to connect to WebDAV",
'opt_sys_imfweud'			=>	"Specify the user name to connect to the WebDAV server",
'opt_sys_imfwep'			=>	"Şifrə üçün connecting to WebDAV",
'opt_sys_imfwepd'			=>	"Specify the password to connect to the WebDAV server",
'hours_diffs'			=>	"saat",
'minutes_diffs'			=>	"dəqiqə",
'time_diffs'			=>	"əvvəl",
'now_diffs'			=>	"İndi",
'diffs_format'			=>	"{date}, saat {time}",
'user_says'			=>	"wrote:",
'settings_panel_11'			=>	"Fonts",
'settings_panel_12'			=>	"Smoothing",
'settings_panel_13'			=>	"Scale",
'opt_sys_aifr'			=>	"Allow iframe insertion into publication texts",
'opt_sys_aifrd'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, it will be allowed to insert iframe tags into the texts of publications, for example, you will be able to insert video and other multimedia inserts from various sites and services",
'opt_sys_aifdl'			=>	"List of allowed domains to insert using an iframe",
'opt_sys_aifdld'			=>	"The iframe tag is a very dangerous tag, so you need to insert content only from trusted sites, you can specify a list of domains that are allowed to be used in this tag. Domains are listed separated by commas, without specifying http or https protocols, as well as without specifying www. For example, to allow insertion from the Youtube service, just specify the domain name youtube.com etc.",
'opt_sys_phpe'			=>	"Aktiv et PHP error output",
'opt_sys_phped'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, if any PHP errors occur on the server, they will be output to the browser. If error output is disabled, they will not be output to the browser. We recommend enabling this option during any technical work on the site, for example, before updating the script, so that in case of problems you can visually see them. And during the normal operation of the site, disable.",
'hidpi_upl'			=>	"HiDPI (Retina) image",
'upgr_f_error_20'			=>	"The new version of Admin Panel {dleversion} requires a minimum installed version of PHP {regversion} and higher. PHP {version} is currently installed on your server. You need to update PHP on the server to version {regversion} and higher",
'opt_sys_acsort'			=>	"Allow users to change the sorting order of categories in the publication",
'opt_sys_acsortd'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, the categories of the publication will be displayed in the order in which they were selected by the author. If disabled, but the categories will be displayed at the publication in the order in which they are sorted by default in the category settings section",
'opt_sys_anedn'			=>	"Notify when editing the news is already being edited",
'opt_sys_anednd'			=>	"When this setting is enabled, when going to edit the news, the user will receive a notification if the publication is already being edited by another user at the moment.",
